
***

### 2. .gitignore

Create a file named `.gitignore` in the root of your repository and paste this inside. This ensures you don't accidentally push your heavy dataset images or Python cache files to GitHub.

```gitignore
# ==========================================
# Dataset and Captures (CRITICAL)
# ==========================================
# Do not push the collected images to GitHub
candling_dataset/
captures/
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png

# ==========================================
# Python
# ==========================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# ==========================================
# Virtual Environments
# ==========================================
venv/
ENV/
env/
.venv

# ==========================================
# IDE and OS files
# ==========================================
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ==========================================
# Jupyter Notebook
# ==========================================
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ==========================================
# Machine Learning / YOLO
# ==========================================
runs/
weights/
*.pt
*.onnx
